top.value: Through the BCD FMOxChange program, FMO puts its clients and partners into contact with one another. Where there is a strong match and opportunity for fruitful knowledge exchange on climate or gender, FMO supports both clients and partners in arranging a visit (or 'exchange') and can contribute to part of the costs.

The proposed Capacity Development (CD) project is a continuation of the current framework agreement between the FS and FMO. The objective is to assist FI clients (initially in Africa, now globally) with risk management issues and business development.

Co-fund a 15-month project aimed the design and pilot an AIF Bottom of the Pyramid commercial strategy in Rwanda, with a strong emphasis on behaviour change to ensure clients purchase and use AIF products compliantly, so that they get the expected health improvements.

FMO provided an unsecured senior A/B syndicated loan facility amounting to US$13.5 million, with a tenor of 5 years. The syndication comprises US$7.5 million from FMO and US$6 million from BIO. The funds will be utilized to finance the growth of the microfinance portfolio in rural areas of Java.
Liwwa has requested FMO to support it in developing its technology roadmap, and to identify the key capabilities that it will need in order to build the business.

While growing rapidly, Vistaar is conscious of potential fraud and operational risks. Therefore, Vistaar plans to build a robust risk management framework to adequately address these risks. FMO will support Vistaar in this endeavor through the Capacity Development (CD) Program.

This project will address strategic priorities related to strengthening Miro’s human resources management, with a gender lens.  Aim is to source new recruits from Field Ready’s vetted pool, specifically for the 40 new positions on the industrial site with a gender profile of 50% women, as well as to develop a mentoring programme targeted towards female employees.

The long-term FMO-A senior loan will support Amret's growth plan to reach out to the MSME sector. This is complemented by a long-term FMO-A subordinated loan, which will support Amret's growth plan by strengthening its capital base.

FDL will use the new facility to continue funding clients in underserved areas of Nicaragua. The objective of this facility, which has a USD 3.0mln committed tranche and a USD 1.5mln uncommitted tranche, is to extend access to finance for micro-, small- and medium-sized enterprises and local agribusinesses.

FMO has provided a five year loan for USD 10 million from the MASSIF fund to VisionFund International (VFI), a global microfinance organisation.  This transaction will especially benefit rural communities and female clients from VisionFund’s African microfinance institutions (MFIs). In addition, FMO has also provided a USD 275,000 Capacity Development (CD) grant to support VFI with an innovative approach to disaster resilient microfinance.
Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Netherlands
